function getdatetimestamp() {
    const datetime = new date();
    const month = (datetime.getutcmonth() + 1 < 10) ? '0' + (datetime.getutcmonth() + 1) : datetime.getutcmonth() + 1;
    const day = (datetime.getutcdate() < 10) ? '0' + datetime.getutcdate() : datetime.getutcdate();
    const hours = (datetime.getutchours() < 10) ? '0' + datetime.getutchours() : datetime.getutchours();
    const minutes = (datetime.getutcminutes() < 10) ? '0' + datetime.getutcminutes() : datetime.getutcminutes();
    const seconds = (datetime.getutcseconds() < 10) ? '0' + datetime.getutcseconds() : datetime.getutcseconds();
    return datetime.getutcfullyear() + '-' + month + '-' + day + ' ' + hours + ':' + minutes + ':' + seconds + " utc";
}

document.getelementbyid("timestamp").innerhtml = "<strong>timestamp: </strong>" +getdatetimestamp();
